
<div class="container-fluid">
  <div class="row">

    <div class="col-sm-6 ">
      <div class="left-content">
        <div class="pretend-canvas">
          <div class="code-input">
            <h3>name = <span id="name_variable"></span></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="code-input">
            <h4>puts "Welcome, #{<span id="code_name">name</span>}!"</h4>
          </div>
          <div class="code-output">
            <h3>Welcome, <span class="name" ></span>!</h3>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-sm-6 ">
      <div class="right-content">
        <h1>Hello!</h1>

        <div class="div1">
          <p>
            Welcome to CODE FARM! You are going to learn some really cool computer tricks over the next few chapters. I'm so excited to learn with you!
          </p>
          <p>Enter your name in the box below and see it appear on the other side!</p>
        <span>
          name = <input type="string" id="name_input" placeholder="add your name here.">
          <button onclick="replaceName(name_input.value,'name'); assignName(name_input.value)">Add your name!</button>
        </span>
        </div>

        <div class="div2" style="display:none">
          <p>
            You see how your name gets attached to the word name at the top? This is called a variable, we will learn more about this later.
          </p>
          <p>
            Why dont you see if you can guess what changes the buttons below make and then click on them to see what happens.
          </p>
          <div class="buttons">
            <span>
              <button onclick="upcase(name_input.value)">.upcase</button>
              <button onclick="downcase(name_input.value)">.downcase</button>
              <button onclick="reverse(name_input.value)">.reverse</button>
              <button onclick="replace(name_input.value)">.replace (vowels with a â˜…!)</button>
            </span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="div1">
          <div class="toggle_button">
            <a href="javascript:void(0);" id="toggle_value">Next</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="div2" style="display:none">
          <div class="toggle_button">
            <%= link_to 'Next', pages_page1_path %>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

<script>
  $("#toggle_value").click((function(){
          var counter = 1;
          return function()
          {
             $(".div" + counter).hide();
             counter = counter + 1;
             $(".div" + counter).show();
          }
  })());
</script>
